result.execSummary:
The defendant Shelby C Duffert-Patraw was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Must sign up for probation no later than Friday April 20, 2018 by 3:00 PM. Early termination of probation would be considered by the Court if the agent requests it.

miscConds.notes: Per C-31. Restitution to be paid from bond money and the rest applied to court costs. Any remaining bond to be refunded.

Cash bond applied. If probation or extended supervision is allowed to expire or is revoked with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent shall notify the court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge and provide current financial information.  A civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for any balances due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect all debt.  Attorney Fees To Be Determined.  Probation does NOT collect attorney fees.
Must attend school or be employed while on probation.

Must continue with the ministry she has worked with while in jail.   Must complete any and all evaluations, counseling, treatment and follow-up recommended by Probation Agent to include trauma focused therapy. Must submit DNA sample and pay the surcharge.  Order for DNA given to the defendant in court. Must report to the Barron County Jail immediately, to submit DNA sample.

timeConds.notes: Court grants 137 days credit if revoked from probation.
